1
00:00:11,120 --> 00:00:14,320
Doctor, it says in 7he Intrepid
Universe Traveller Handbook

2
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:16,640
that if you want to properly call
yourself a space traveller

3
00:00:16,760 --> 00:00:18,920
you're supposed to have
an adventure at least once a week.

4
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:20,440
-Well!
-Well,

5
00:00:20,920 --> 00:00:24,400
-we haven't had an adventure in ages.
-You're absolutely right.

6
00:00:24,480 --> 00:00:26,080
Adventure it is!

7
00:00:26,160 --> 00:00:27,680
(YELPS)

8
00:00:27,760 --> 00:00:31,280
-What was that? what did you just do?
-Exactly what you asked me to.

9
00:00:31,360 --> 00:00:34,000
I set the Tardis to Adventure setting.

10
00:00:34,080 --> 00:00:35,560
(BOTH EXCLAIM)

11
00:00:35,640 --> 00:00:37,920
Are you sure you didn't set it to
Kill Amy And The Doctor setting?

12
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:40,240
Now, now, now, now,
hang on, that was meant to happen!

13
00:00:46,520 --> 00:00:48,520
-So was that.
-I'm sure it was.

14
00:00:48,960 --> 00:00:51,480
Perhaps I should take it down
just a smidge.

15
00:00:53,080 --> 00:00:55,200
-0h!
-What? What is it?

16
00:00:55,360 --> 00:00:57,200
Systems malfunctioning, Tardis crashing.

17
00:00:57,280 --> 00:00:59,080
Oh, great!

18
00:00:59,160 --> 00:01:02,400
Okay, Tardis going down in
three, two, one... Landing!

19
00:01:02,480 --> 00:01:03,800
(AMY SCREAMS)

20
00:01:04,600 --> 00:01:06,200
-Ha!
-(GROANS)

21
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:09,200
-Now...
-Ah, so,

22
00:01:09,720 --> 00:01:11,640
where are we, Einstein?

23
00:01:12,040 --> 00:01:14,320
I'm not quite sure. It appears

24
00:01:14,640 --> 00:01:17,200
as though we've landed in the middle
of an Olympic running track.

25
00:01:17,280 --> 00:01:18,880
(CROWD CHEERING)

26
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:23,560
Where am I?

27
00:01:25,760 --> 00:01:27,480
And what the heck's happened
to your hair?

28
00:01:27,560 --> 00:01:30,480
Yes, yes, yes. From the look of you,

29
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:34,040
you're an Olympic torch bearer,
London 2012, if I'm not mistaken.

30
00:01:34,120 --> 00:01:38,280
I'm the Doctor, this is Amy, and welcome
to my spaceship, the Tardis. (CHUCKLES)

31
00:01:38,360 --> 00:01:41,440
Oh, and my hair, well, that's a story
for another time.

32
00:01:41,520 --> 00:01:44,040
Wait, there was something chasing me.

33
00:01:44,360 --> 00:01:47,040
That's why I didn't see your.. box.

34
00:01:48,960 --> 00:01:49,960
(AMY YELPS)

35
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:53,320
BOTH: Don't blink!

36
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:55,600
(AMY YELPS)

37
00:01:55,680 --> 00:01:56,840
Hey!

38
00:01:57,560 --> 00:01:59,760
-How did it do that?
-Oh my God, Doctor, what's it doing?

39
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:03,120
It's trying to steal the Olympic flame
and destroy the very spirit

40
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:06,320
of respect, excellence and friendship
it represents.

41
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:08,720
Well, at least it's trying to.

42
00:02:20,360 --> 00:02:21,400
Ah!

43
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:25,440
Wow! Thanks, Doctor.

44
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:29,320
I'd better get going, though,
I've got to light the Olympic flame.

45
00:02:29,760 --> 00:02:31,680
Here, you deserve this.

46
00:02:32,080 --> 00:02:34,040
Oh, thank you very much.

47
00:02:34,640 --> 00:02:37,480
Good as gold you are, Doctor. Bye.

48
00:02:38,040 --> 00:02:39,400
BOTH: Bye!

49
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:42,200
Ah, cool!

50
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:45,520
Right, where were we? Ah, yes.

51
00:02:45,760 --> 00:02:47,280
Adventure!

